-- China Stock-Index Futures Trading Has Been `Orderly' Since Start, Zhu Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-25T12:37:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/china-stock-index-futures-trading-has-been-orderly-since-start-zhu-says.html

          
          
             Trading in China’s stock-index
futures has been “orderly” since their introduction earlier
this year and there hasn’t been “blind speculation,” Zhu
Yuchen, chief executive officer of China’s Financial Futures
Exchange, said in a financial forum in Shanghai.  
